@piiswrong @eric-haibin-lin @anirudh2290 @cjolivier01 @rahul003 @madjam @bhavinthaker

The goal of this PR is to ensure that an exception or a warning log is thrown if a duplicated model is identified.

The current code only alerts for duplicates identified while tagging a model with ``x-model`` attribute (``tag_models`` and ``bless_models`` callback), but it does not alerts in case of duplicated models obtained by pre-tagged models (models that have ``x-model`` attribute on the specs).

This PR changes it making sure that we're alerting also while generating the respective python type representation of the model.


**Example**
The following specs are not raising any error with the current master branch even if we do have different specs for ``model``
```json
{
  "definitions": {
    "a": {
      "type": "object",
      "x-model": "model"
    },
    "b": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "prop": {"type": "string"}
      },
      "required": ["prop"],
      "x-model": "model"
    }
  }
...
}
```

Hello @psung ,

I have implemented your proposal. I added just one new `public SearchPage<T> getPage(int pageSize)` method to `DXSearch.FindDataObjectsRequestBuilder<T>` class and made iterations to be done using 'public SearchPage<T> next()' method in `DXSearch.SearchPage<T>` class.

That is because this kind of API looks similar to `Iterator<E>`, but I'm not sure about that - it's just a proposal. If you are not comfortable with that - inform me, please, and I would update this PR. It looks like a 5-10 min change...

P.S. I tried to make `DXSearch.SearchPage<T>` to implement `Iterator<DXSearch.SearchPage<T>>` interface, but in that case iterator and actual value are represented by the same object and I do not know is it good or bad.

```
// Iterating current page's items
for (DXRecord r : page) {
    ...
}
// Switching to the next page
if (page.hasNext()) {
    page = page.next(); // <- I suspect this is not compatible with 'Iterator<E>' Java concept
}
```

All the best,
Ilya

